'''Richard LeParmentier''' ([[July 16]], [[1940s|1946]]<ref name="SWYT 2020-07-16" />&ndash;[[April 15]], [[2013]]<ref name="Death" />) played [[Conan Antonio Motti]] in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']]. His character was credited as "[[General]] Motti."

Born in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, LeParmentier relocated from the United States to the United Kingdom. He had done voice work in ''Soldiers: Heroes of World War 2'' and also appeared in such films as ''Who Framed Roger Rabbit?''. He was also once married to Sarah Douglas, known for her role as ''Superman'' villainess Ursa. He co-starred with her and [[Terence Stamp]] (who portrayed [[Finis Valorum]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']]) in ''Superman 2''.

LeParmentier died on April 15, 2013.<ref name="Death" />

